subparagraph.text:
requires that the child be a child who has
				received an initial evaluation described in section 614(a) and has been
				identified as a child with a disability, in accordance with part B;

clause.text:
permits persons to receive a State tax credit for donations to an entity that provides funds to parents of eligible students described in subparagraph (A), to be used by the parents to pay some or all of the costs of attendance at the
				selected school (which may include tuition, fees, and transportation
				costs);

notwithstanding
				this subparagraph or any other provision of law, a parent may choose, and a
				school may offer, a single-sex school, class, or activity;
